subSubSection.paragraph:
Subspecies. The Korean populations are considered to belong to the nominal subspecies (cf.
Lee 1982
, 1992 ) although several other subspecific names have been suggested: subsp.
here
(cf.
Doi 1928
;
Mori et al . 1934
;
Seok 1939 b
), subsp.
clytie
(cf.
Nakayama 1932
;
Mori et al . 1934
;
Seok 1939 a
;
Okano 1998
), subsp. ussuriensis (cf.
Kurentzov 1937
), etc. No morphological differences are recognizable between the Korean populations and the nominal subspecies.
